\begin_layout Section
Conclusion
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We have shown, that atleast from the Peres Mermin's proof, it doesn't follow
 that contextuality is a necessary feature of QM.
 We have identified a new property, which we call non-multiplicativity.
 We have been able to construct a non-contextual hidden variable theory,
 that is completely consistent with QM of spins and it's predictions, we
 call a discretely c-ingle theory.
 This theory is non-multiplicative.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We also noted that upon restriction of measurement schemes, Bohmian Mechanics
 (BM) can also be viewed as a non-contextual hidden variable theory, which
 is non-multiplicative.
 
\end_layout

